a\sin x+b\sin(x+\alpha )=c\sin(x+\beta )\,
c=\sqrt {a^2+b^2+2ab\cos \alpha },\,
\beta =\arctan \left(\frac {b\sin \alpha }{a+b\cos \alpha }\right) + \begin{cases} 0 & \text{if } a+b \cos \alpha \geq 0,\\ \pi & \text{if } a+b\cos \alpha <0.\end{cases}
